(21809, 'Lidocaine hcl pharmacell 2% vial im iv sc 20 ml', 'ليدوكايين هيدروكلوريد فارماسيل 2% فيال 20 مل', '11.25', '10', 'Lidocaine', 'Pharmacell', 'Vial', 'فيال', '', 'Analgesic.local anesthetic', '2%', 'Lidocaine is an anesthetic of the amide group indicated for production of local or regional anesthesia by infiltration techniques such as percutaneous injection and intravenous regional anesthesia by peripheral nerve block techniques such as brachial plexus and intercostal and by central neural techniques such as lumbar and caudal epidural blocks [F4349, L5930].', '', '', 1124, '2023-10-06', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
(18466, 'Epitens 30 tab.', 'ابيتينس 30 قرص', '', '7', 'Triamterene+xipamide', 'Eipico', 'Tab', 'أقراص', 'علاج ارتفاع ضغط الدم', 'Antihypertensive', '', '', '6221032112446', '', 1357, '2023-01-13', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
(24317, 'Ospexin 1000 mg 12 tabs.', 'اوسبيكسين 1000مجم 12 اقراص', '', '29', 'Cefalexin', 'El nile. > novartis', 'Tab', 'أقراص', '', 'Antibiotic.cephalosporin.first-generation', '1000 mg', 'about cefalexin a first-generation cephalosporin antibiotic. mechanism of action cephalexin is a 1st generation cephalosporin which exerts its bactericidal action against both gram positive & gram negative organisms by inhibiting bacterial cell wall synth', '6221088010444', '', 815, '2022-12-07', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
(17312, 'Derma v10 24/7 body lotion 200 ml', 'ديرما في 10 24/7 غسول للجسم 200 مل', '', '120', 'Almond oil+shea butter', 'Healthpoint ltd > paxton', 'Lotion', 'لوشن', '', 'Moisturizing topicals', '200 ml', 'for dry skin. rapid skin hydration. with almond oil & shea butter. softens hydrates & soothes skin. ** directions: apply liberally & as often as necessary. use twice daily for best results.', '', '', 839, '2022-08-01', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
(31018, 'Ogivri 440 mg vial (pd for i.v. inf.)', 'اوجيفري 440مجم فيال', '9500', '14,745', 'Trastuzumab', 'Biocon > mylan', 'Vial', 'فيال', '', 'Antineoplastic', '440 mg', 'For the adjuvant treatment of HER2-overexpressing breast cancer, trastuzumab is indicated in several clinical settings: as part of a treatment regimen consisting of doxorubicin, cyclophosphamide, and either paclitaxel or docetaxel; as part of a treatment regimen with docetaxel and carboplatin; or as monotherapy following multi-modality anthracycline-based therapy.[L14015]
Trastuzumab is indicated as a first-line treatment, in combination with paclitaxel, for metastatic HER2-overexpressing breast cancer, and as monotherapy in patients who have previously received one or more chemotherapy regimens in the metastatic setting.[L14015] In Europe, trastuzumab can also be used in combination with paclitaxel or docetaxel for the treatment of metastatic HER2-positive breast cancer in adult patients and with an aromatase inhibitor in postmenopausal patients.[L49324]
For HER2-positive early breast cancer, the EMA approved trastuzumab as monotherapy following surgery, chemotherapy (neoadjuvant or adjuvant), and radiation or following adjuvant chemotherapy with doxorubicin and cyclophosphamide in combination with paclitaxel or docetaxel. It can also be used in combination with adjuvant chemotherapy consisting of docetaxel and carboplatin or with neoadjuvant chemotherapy followed by adjuvant trastuzumab therapy for locally advanced (including inflammatory) disease or tumors > 2 cm in diameter.[L49324]
Trastuzumab is also indicated, in combination with cisplatin and capecitabine or 5-fluorouracil, for the treatment of patients with HER2-overexpressing metastatic gastric or gastroesophageal junction adenocarcinoma who have not received prior treatment for metastatic disease by the FDA and EMA.[L14015]
Trastuzumab is indicated for subcutaneous administration - in combination with either [hyaluronidase][L14132] or both hyaluronidase and [pertuzumab][L14510] - for the treatment of adults with HER2-positive breast cancers.', '', '', 1173, '2024-11-20', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
(25341, 'Promatic 5% top. gel 25 gm', 'بروماتيك5% توب جل 25 جم', '', '7', 'Etofenamate', 'Sigma > pharma cure pharmaceuticals', 'Gel', 'جل', '', 'Nsaid.analgesic', '5%', 'etofenamate etofenamate is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug (nsaid). nsaids relieve pain and reduce the inflammation and fever produced by the body s immune system. etofenamate has been successfully used for a number a years to treat patients with a', '', '', 846, '2022-08-02', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
